Question 1

Stabilité temporelle de la variable “Couverture” au sein de portefeuille.

tab=bd[,list(Expo=sum(Expo)), by=list(Exercice,Couverture)]

ggplot(tab,aes(x=Exercice,y=part_expo,group=Couverture,col=Couverture))+geom_line()

Question 7

Calculer la corrélation entre variables tarifaires potentielles.

var_freq=c("Exercice","Couverture","Nbpieces","Nbpers","Qualite","Kassu","Age2",
           "Usage","Local","Direct","DMG","Zonier_DDE","Ante_DDE",
           "Zonier_Vol","Ante_Vol","Dep")

bd=as.matrix(bd)
res=matrix(NA,nrow=length(var_freq),ncol=length(var_freq))
for (i in 1:length(var_freq)) {
  for (j in 1:length(var_freq)) {
    res[i,j]=CramerV(bd[,(var_freq[i])],bd[,(var_freq[j])])
  }}
colnames(res)=var_freq
rownames(res)=var_freq

color2D.matplot(res, extremes = c("white", "blue"), vcol = "black",nslices = 60,
                show.legend=TRUE,axes=TRUE,show.values=TRUE,xlab="Columns",ylab="Rows") 

neworder=hclust(dist(res))$order
res2=res[neworder,neworder]

qplot(x=Var1, y=Var2, data=melt(res2), fill=value, geom="tile") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust=1)) +
  xlab(NULL)+ylab(NULL)+labs(fill="V de Cramér")
